        "description": "Picosecond regime preferred over nanoseconds (5-100 ns) for GaAs to minimize heat-affected zone due to its moderate thermal conductivity (~50 W/m·K); femtoseconds (<1 ps) possible but less common for industrial cleaning. Recommended 10 ps for precise contaminant ablation. Source: Laser physics research in Opt. Express (2020) on ultrafast cleaning of semiconductors."
